data.title: Taylor County, Florida Population 2024
data.text:
Taylor County, Florida 's estimated 2024 population is 21,851 with a growth rate of 1.25% in the past year according to the most recent United States census data. Taylor County, Florida is the 54th largest county in Florida. The 2010 population was 22,594 and has seen a growth of -3.29% since that time.

The highest rate of high school graduation is among asian people with a rate of 100% .

The highest rate of bachelors degrees is among islander people with a rate of 100% .
